the only sound the soft hum of distant traffic 
a reminder that life goes on even when we're still

The world outside recedes and I am left alone 
with only my thoughts to keep me company 
no distractions no interruptions just the steady beat 
of my own heart guiding me through the darkness 

In this silence I find a strange sort of peace 
a sense of freedom from the burdens I carry 
a chance to rediscover myself in the stillness 
and find my way back to who I truly amassistant
